How to prepare your own cloud immitation with VMware ang got ready your DevOps envirounment.

Used hardware:
- MSI Nettop
- RAM 64Gb
- SSD1 1TB
- SSD2 500Gb
- Host OS Windows 10
- Host Hyperviser VMware Workstation 17
- Virtual ESXi1 RAM 12Gb, Disk 300Gb
- Virtual ESXi RAM 12Gb? Disk 400Gb
- Virtual host Windows 10

DevOps envirounment to be installed on Virtual host Windows 10.
It include:

- Visual Studio code and its plugins
- VMware tools (like OVF)
- Vagrant and plugins for VMware (vagrant plugin install vagrant-vmware-desktop)

==============================================================================================

Steps taken

1. Intsall VMware Workstation 17
2. Install virtual ESXi 7 inside VMware Workstation
3. Install virtual OS Windows 10 inside VMware Workstation
 
Installation in Virtual Windows 10

4. Install Visual Studio Code vesion 1.96
5. Inside Visual Studio install all needed plugins
6. Install vagrant via MSI file for Windows
6. in Visual Studio CLI install vagrant:
    vagrant plugin install vagrant-vmware-desktop
    vagrant plugin install vagrant-vmware-esxi
7. Install vagrant-vmware-utility via MSI file for Windows
8. Install VMware-ovf-tool via MSI file for Windows
9. 

